30/12/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Bosnian state prosecutors submitted an indictment on Friday (December 28th) against retired General Novak Djukic, the former Chief of Staff of the Army of Republika Srpska.
Djukic is charged with command responsibility for an artillery attack on the northwestern town of Tuzla on May 25th 1995.
Seventy-one people were killed and many other injured.
The prosecution also issued an indictment against the former commander of a Serbian military unit in the Doboj region, Predrag Kujundzic.
He is charged with taking part in killings, detention, rape, persecution and forcing women into sexual slavery.
(RTRS, NTV Hayat, AFP, Makfax, UPI - 28/12/07)
